        <div><div class="post-title">When does Chain-of-Thought actually fail?</div><div class="post-excerpt">My experiments on FLAN-T5 revealed something counterintuitive: more structured prompting can make things worse. I trace through what happened in my ablation studies and what it tells us about the structural limits of encoder-decoder architectures at inference time.</div></div>
