        <div><div class="post-title">What connectomes taught me about neural networks</div><div class="post-excerpt">Using human and Drosophila connectomes as architectural priors for reservoir computing produced surprising results — including perfect classification accuracy on spike-train manifolds. The more interesting finding was about criticality tuning.</div></div>
